            "creation_date": 1443989254,
            "body": "<p>There's no \"try-with-resource\" template included in Eclipse.<\/p>\n\n<p>There is an open issue for it: <a href=\"https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=351864\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bug 351864 - [1.7][templates] Add 'try-with-resource' template<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 32937848,
            "question_id": 23698534
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/I4fiW.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 4243,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 6309,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6309/vonc",
                "reputation": 1361231,
                "display_name": "VonC",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1639239604,
            "creation_date": 1639239129,
            "body": "<p>Eclipse 4.22 (Q4 2021, 7 years later) might offer that feature:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.eclipse.org/eclipse/news/4.22/jdt.php#surround-with-try-with-resources-quickfix\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Surround with try-with-resources quickfix<\/a><\/h2>\n<p>A new quickfix has been created to offer Surround with <code>try-with-resources<\/code> for resource leaks and potential resource leaks when the resource in question implements AutoCloseable.<\/p>\n<p>Examples of quickfix:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8aV4P.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8aV4P.png\" alt=\"Unclosed Resource -- https://www.eclipse.org/eclipse/news/4.22/images/unclosed-closeable.png\" /><\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/1SxiR.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/1SxiR.png\" alt=\"Potentially Unclosed Resource\" /><\/a><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n",
